args:
As Beren faces the prince and Phares faces
Nedrick, Harle obtains the key for the revival
of Satan and makes for Grams. With great
turmoil looming, the prince and Nedrick
engage in a final clash over their ideals.
That was quite the fall, but yes,\nI'm still here.
We need to hurry and find everyone else.\nI assume they're all making their way\ndown the tree now.
And we should do the same now that\nthe quaking has subsided.
If you're free, you can play with me.
Don't worry. I'm just here to chat.
It seems you were a hollow little prince\nafter all, {player_name}.
Your existence? Your ideals? Everything\nabout you turned out to be so much\nlovely window-dressing.
Surely you have realized how insignificant\nyou are by now. How does it feel?
You're right. I might not be a prince—\nI might not even be human. I could just\nbe an empty, insignificant existence.
But I also learned that I have friends who\nwon't abandon me even if those things\nturn out to be true.
I have an entire world to protect,\nand that's why I—
What could anyone possibly need with\nan empty husk like you? You should be\nwallowing in rejection! In despair!
You're just an empty sham, and this world\nhas no place for you!
So why, then? Why do you have something\nthat I don't?
You're a hopeless little brother.\nIf that's how it is, I'll just have to teach\nyou what despair feels like myself!
I stand little chance going four-on-one,\nso I'll have to start with the bit players.
You protected him with your own body?\nHe must be a special friend indeed.
He is—which is why we swore to see\nthe new world together.
And here I thought simpering over ideals\nwas part of the {player_name} special.
Don't lump me in with his milquetoast\nfraternizing.
They can't even settle on a purpose or\nideals without having to cozy up to each\nother first... It makes me ill.
And the two of you are different?
Of course. We know what we roles we\nmust fulfill to reach the ideals we share.
So you remain independent while still\nsupporting one another? That sounds\nlike a fine relationship indeed.
But from my perspective,\nthere is scant difference\nbetween you and {player_name}.
You band together because you cannot\naccomplish your goals on your own.\nThis only proves your weakness.
I am reluctant for us to say our goodbyes,\nbut I fear this will be all for today.
When next we meet, I will take that\nbeautiful friendship of yours and shatter\nit into oblivion.
Preparations appear to be ready, Beren.\nLet us be off.
That was fast. Guess that guy knows\nwhat he's doing after all.
Indeed, Satan's revival is at hand.
Later, empty prince.\nWhen next we meet, I'll teach you\nmore despair than you can imagine.
I was not sure how this would play out,\nbut they truly appear to be retreating.
I'm more concerned about whatever this\n＂Satan＂ issue is.
Yeah, I've got a bad feeling about this.
Thanks to Their Highnesses Beren and\nPhares, I was quite easily able to get\nwhat I required.
A Sacred Shard containing Metatron's\nmana is the key required for the rite that\nwill see Satan revived.
The world will be dragged kicking and\nscreaming into chaos's grim abyss!
The time has come to set the stage...\nTo the Holy City of Grams!
And all in one piece, which is what\nmatters most.
I'm happy to see you all as well.\nEr, but where's Gatov?
He stayed up top so we could escape.
No, he wasn't alone. He was with...\nUm, wait. Everyone's here, right?
What the hey? I KNOW he wasn't alone!\nBut who was with him?
We're all safe, and that's what matters.\nBut it would seem we are not alone.
Alas, it does not appear we'll have time to\nbask in a happy reunion.
I won't allow you to get in my way again,\n{player_name}.

I know where you come from and what
you're trying to do, Nedrick, but I don't
believe you're going about things the
right way.
And if you're allowed to continue, countless\npeople will suffer. I can't let that happen.
Even if it costs my life, I WILL stop you.
Hollow words from a hollow man.\nFine, then. Do it if you can.
(The dual seventh scions are putting\neverything on the line for their ideals.)
(Which of their beliefs will become the\nfoundation of justice in this world?\nWhich one will determine our future?)
